definitions.definition: To bite something persistently, especially something tough.
examples: The dog gnawed the bone until it broke in two.

definitions.definition: To produce excessive anxiety or worry.
examples: Her comment gnawed at me all day and I couldn't think about anything else.

definitions.definition: To corrode ; to fret away; to waste .

main_definition: ( ambitransitive ) To bite something persistently, especially something tough.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To produce excessive anxiety or worry.
To corrode ; to fret away; to waste .
